caption: This place sure knows how to please their customers. Always with a friendly demeanor. The food is fairly priced, regularly tasty and clean.

I ordered the Chicken Pho, Kimchi Fries and Bulgogi Rolls. I am part Korean and that was not bulgogi. I asked for my money back just for those and I was told I couldn’t get a refund. Please don’t call them bulgogi.  Oh, I ordered a Vietnamese Ice Coffee as well. Very nice and rich and though it didn’t come in the typical drip tin I am accustomed to I did like it! I came to this place with some hesitation at the suggestion of a friend as Pho options for vegetarians are generally mediocre at best, but Red Boat has definitely raised the bar. It is a medium-sized, order-at-counter restaurant, and it was not crowded on a Monday night with plenty of seating available. I ordered the Tom Yum Pho (100% Vegan) and added fried tofu (total ~$13). This Pho was a lemongrass & Chilli paste flavored soup with mushrooms, basil leaf, broccoli, cabbage, carrots, cilantro & onions served with lemon, jalapenos, and bamboo shoots. The dish was clearly made to order and the ingredients used were pretty fresh, which was pretty impressive for a fast food type place. Similar to the other reviews about this vegetarian Pho, I was seriously impressed with the broth they offered!! Many places fail to deliver on vegetarian broths, but this tom yum broth had flavor-packed punches throughout the entire bowl; not an ounce of it remained by the time I finished. Their noodles were pretty good, the vegetables tasted relatively fresh, and the tofu was fried pretty well. I think the only change I would make is for the dish to be just slightly less sour.  Additionally, the cashier was kind and helpful, and their check-out process is well-organized and quick. I think the only negative aspect of the restaurant was locked bathrooms that require getting a key on a spatula. However, the entire place seemed pretty new and very clean as well, so overall environment of this place was great.  Overall, I would definitely recommend this place, especially for those vegetarians searching the winter for a comforting, flavorful Pho, and I look forward to going back!

I really grappled with leaving a 4 star or 3 star review. I settled on 3 stars because three is average and this place was that, average. I got Banh Mi, but it was so overloaded with meat that I could barely enjoy what made it Banh Mi, the cucumber, carrots, and other items that add flavor. I get that it is "viet fusion" but Banh Mi might be the best way to eat food on a baguette and I just didn't get what I usually expect from banh mi. Also, the "baguette" was just a hoagie roll.  Having said that, the food wasn't bad, they clearly know how to cook and make food, but I would moreso call it a sandwich than banh mi.

I also ordered a rice boat with lemongrass chicken, stir fry vegs, corn and egg with teriyaki sauce.  Yummo!!!! The thai ice tea was good too! My friend got the tacos and could not stop stating how tasty they were. I noticed several patrons checking out each other's dishes and snapping pictures.  The young lady who took my order later came around the dinning area to check on customers. All of the staff are friendly and accommodating. This is a definite welcome addition to the neighborhood. I'm already planning my next visit...shucks it maybe tomorrow not sure I can wait for the work week. I need a VIP card Red Boat!
